cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the problem of adversarial examples in neural networks. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these fields heavily rely on neural networks and face similar challenges with adversarial examples. Additionally, since the paper proposes a formal verification technique, it could also be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
